 then the FSM\ndecides which device receives a grant to use the resource and changes to\na state that sets that device\'s _g[i]_ signal to 1. Each _g[i]_ is an\noutput from the FSM. There is a priority system, in that device 0 has a\nhigher priority than device 1, and device 2 has the lowest priority.\nHence, for example, device 2 will only receive a grant if it is the only\ndevice making a request when the FSM is in state _A_. Once a device, _i_,\nis given a grant by the FSM, that device continues to receive the grant\nas long as its request, _r[i]_ = 1.\n\nImplement a module that represents this FSM. Use separate always blocks\nfor the state table and the state flip-flops, as done in lectures.\nDescribe the FSM outputs, _g[i]_, using either continuous assignment\nstatement(s) or an always block (at your discretion). Assign any state\ncodes that you wish to use. Assume all sequential logic is triggered on\nthe positive edge of the clock.\n\n\n</input_spec>\n<failed_sim_log>\n{\n    "stdout": "",\n    "stderr": "./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:9: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:1: Errors in port declarations.\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:29: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:30: error: Malformed statement\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:31: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:32: error: Malformed statement\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:36: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:43: error: Malformed statement\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob148_2013_q2afsm/tb.sv:91: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4